               <provenance>lǝğ Gabra Ḥǝywat (11ra, ls. 4-5, 24vb, ls. 9-10, 27va, l.7, 34va, ls. 3-4, 38va, ls.
                     1-2, 38va, 11-12); Gabra Masqal (11ra, l.5, 27va, ls. 6-7, 34va, l.4, 38va, l.1);
                     Walatta Yoḥannǝs (11ra, l.7, 24vb, l.10, 27va,
                     ls. 9-10, 34va, ls. 5-6, 38va, ls. 3-4); Walatta Śǝllāse (24vb, l.11, 27va, l.10, 34va, 6, 38va, ls. 4-5); Walatta Masqal
                        (27va, ls. 8-9); Walatta Ṣǝyon (34va, l.7); Walatta Māryām (38va, l.6); ʾAmata Ṣǝyon (38va,
                     l.5). Currently, the book is in possession of Mǝdra
                     Ruba Śǝllāse; however, a short note following the explicit of the Homily states
                     that (initially) lǝğ Gabra Ḥǝywat donated the manuscript to the church of St
                     Mary of ʾAbaʿko. It seems to be one of several churches in the area which
                     disappeared, but whose tabots and books were brought to the church of Mǝdra
                     Ruba.</provenance></history>
